{{Navlist/Bottom}}

Welcome!  You have come upon the beginning of a lighter-side look at Open Source, open source, Free Software, free software, Unix, Unix-likes and the whole mess known today as the Internet.

This book touches on the concepts of hacking, cracking, scripting and programming; illustrating the differences between them all and why there is a gap between the people doing these things and the masses unaware of the differences between them.
Other topics will include the reasons for using different licenses for programs and what some of the more common ones mean to users and programmers.

== Contents ==
#[[/What do you mean Open Source isn't Free Software|What do you mean Open Source isn't Free Software?]] - Explaining the differences in the terms used for the various types of open source software. {{stage short|50%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/I have to give you what|I have to give you what?]] - Talking about the rights given in licenses and those that are not. {{stage short|75%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/Theft or Copying|Theft or Copying?]] - Talking about "stealing" source, how it is actually copying with no loss of property involved. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/In the Beginning|In the Beginning...]] - Explaining where the various open source movements began and the start of the Internet, do not go into detail the groups, just their basics - further detail will be in their specific chapters. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/Unix|Unix]] - The beginnings of Unix, it's relation to Multics and it's involvement with BSD.  Mention Bell's K&R and the beginning of C. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/BSD|BSD]] - Talk about the BSDs, their founders and their strengths and weaknesses, go into more detail than [[Use the Source/In the Beginning | In the Beginning...]]. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/Let's get ready to RUMBLE|Let's get ready to RUMBLE!]] - The lawsuit involving BSDi, USL and the University of California; discuss the result of the suit as well as how it effected the BSD and Linux movements. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/BSD's Not Unix|BSD's Not Unix]] - The Unix trademark, Unix-likes, System V. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/Gnu's Not Unix|Gnu's Not Unix]] - Talk about Richard Stallman and the Free Software Foundation and about the various licenses they have made and how they view other licenses. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/Linux|Linux]] - Talk about Linus Torvalds and the kernel he made, describe the relation to Minix and Unix.
#[[/Gnu's Not Linux|Gnu's Not Linux!]] -  Talk about the mincing of words between the Linux and GNU camps.
#[[/Gnu/Linux|Gnu/Linux]] -  The partial result of the GNU and Linux camps spat.
#[[/OpenSolaris|OpenSolaris]] - Discuss OpenSolaris, what it means to other open source projects.
#[[/Divide and Conquer|Divide and Conquer]] - Talk about community friction, the concept of allies and enemies within the open source world.
#[[/Cancer|Cancer]] - Talk about the stance given by Microsoft regarding the General Public License, Linux and GNU. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
#[[/Counter-Culture|Counter-Culture]] - Talk about the rising of an anti-Microsoft movement, its relation to the open source groups and its effects on their usage and development. {{stage short|00%|October 9, 2005}}
